From: Randy Miskanic

Subject: Gateway specs

Importance: High

JR,

Attached is a first draft version of what we need for Shift4's various gateways:

1.  There is the UTG spec and all of our current gateways comply with this
    spec.
2.  There is a 4Go spec and the 4GoA gateway device (and i4Go) needs to
    comply with the 4Go spec.
3.  There is an i4Go spec and this is a product offering that runs as a standalone
    version of #2 above on IOS and Android devices.
4.  Last is a new "Mobile" spec. This spec addresses the many mobile gateway
    devices that Shift4 has had to deal with over the years. Many times,
    developers have not properly implemented the UTG spec and they end up
    sending us bad/inconsistent data. The intent of the mobile spec is to move
    the complexity out of the device and onto i4Go/4Go. The mobile device
    simply becomes a conduit for the data, and it is 4Go/i4Go that takes one end
    of the connection and then properly communicates with the UTG.

As such, a 4Go device needs to implement the 4Go spec, the i4Go spec, *AND*
the Mobile spec.

Please let me know what you think of what I have written.

Thanks,
Randy
